    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9354" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φάλος</span></b> : (1) the metal
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">ridge</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">crest</span> of the helmet,
          extending from back to front, with a socket to hold the plume (see cut
          No. 122).—(2) in narrower signification, the rounded
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">boss</span>, projecting <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">forepiece</span>, in which
          the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φάλος</span> terminated, <i><span class="en">Il. 6.9</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            13.132</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
